properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Wet snow expected at the summit overnight and Sunday morning. A cold upper trough will reside over the southern interior tonight and Sunday. Steady rain is forecast to transition to wet snow at the summit of the Okanagan Connector overnight and then change back to showers by Sunday afternoon. Snowfall amounts of 2 to 5 cm are possible. ### Weather in the mountains can change suddenly resulting in hazardous driving conditions. Road conditions are available at www.drivebc.ca. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.
Expires: 2020-06-14T20:11:33-00:00

properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: At 10:40 p.m. MDT, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a cluster of dangerous thunderstorms capable of producing very strong wind gusts, up to tennis ball size hail and heavy rain. This thunderstorm cluster is located from Lousana to Three Hills and is moving northeastward at 50 km/h. ### Very large hail can damage property, break windows, dent vehicles and cause serious injury. Remember, severe thunderstorms can produce tornadoes. Severe thunderstorm warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall.

Severe thunderstorm watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ABstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ABStorm.
